subSubSection.paragraph:
Head with epistome feebly convex, evenly, densely punctate throughout; clypeus slightly sinuate at middle, rounded at sides, rather thickly bordered, edge almost imperceptibly ciliate; genae obtuse, almost imperceptibly ciliate, slightly protruding from the eyes; frontal suture finely impressed, not tuberculate; frons and epistome similarly punctate; first labial palpomere longer than second (
Fig. 8
).

